Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State has signed the state’s budget of N339 billion passed by the Ogun State House of Assembly for the 2021 fiscal year into law.
The governor signed the budget tagged: budget of recovery and sustainability, under the watchful eyes of members of the State House of Assembly led by the Speaker, Rt. Hon. Taiwo Oluomo, including members of the State Executive Council.
Governor Abiodun assured citizens in Ogun State that the 2021 budget will be implemented to improve infrastructure development, education, health care delivery, housing, and security.
Commending the leadership of the House for the commitment and dedication of the House members, Governor Abiodun expressed optimism that 2021 will be better.
The governor demanded the understanding of residents of the state in ensuring that the successful implementation of the budget is for the good of all.
